# Fraud Detection ML Pipeline

This project detects fraudulent financial transactions using machine learning. It analyzes transaction data to identify three real-world fraud patterns:

- High-value transactions (> $220)
- Compromised terminals (28-day patterns)  
- Customer spending spikes (14-day anomalies)

## What It Does

1. **Loads data** from multiple `.pkl` files in `data/` folder
2. **Creates 25+ smart features** (time patterns, customer behavior, terminal risk)
3. **Handles imbalance** (few frauds, many legit) using SMOTE
4. **Trains 5 models**: XGBoost, RandomForest, LightGBM, GradientBoosting, LogisticRegression
5. **Evaluates & compares** using precision, recall, F1, ROC-AUC
6. **Generates reports** + plots showing best model (87% precision achieved)

## Dataset Format

Put `.pkl` files in `data/` folder. Each file needs these columns:
TRANSACTION_ID, TX_DATETIME, CUSTOMER_ID, TERMINAL_ID, TX_AMOUNT, TX_FRAUD

text

Example:
data/
├── 2018-09-14.pkl
├── 2018-09-15.pkl
└── ...

text

## Quick Start

git clone https://github.com/Akb6/fraud-detection-ml-pipeline
cd fraud-detection-ml-pipeline

Setup environment
python -m venv fraud_env
fraud_env\Scripts\activate # Windows

Install packages
pip install pandas numpy scikit-learn xgboost lightgbm imbalanced-learn matplotlib seaborn

Run everything
python demo.py

text

## Outputs Generated

- `fraud_detection_report.txt` - All metrics + best model
- `fraud_detection_results.png` - ROC curves + feature importance
- Saved models in `models/` folder

## Results

| Model      | Precision | Recall | F1-Score | ROC-AUC |
|------------|-----------|--------|----------|---------|
| XGBoost    | 87%       | 84%    | 85%      | 0.92    |
| RandomForest | 86%     | 83%    | 84%      | 0.91    |


